## Methods
### get_credentials

`async def get_credentials(self, username: str) -> dict:`

Get credentials [returns](https://github.com/Whitecap-DNA/WCP-Library/wiki/Credentials-%E2%80%90-Expected-Dictionaries) the credentials for the requested username.

```
credentials = await CredentialsManager.get_credentials(<username>)
```

### get_credential_from_id

`async def get_credential_by_id(self, password_id: int) -> dict:`

Get credentials [returns](https://github.com/Whitecap-DNA/WCP-Library/wiki/Credentials-%E2%80%90-Expected-Dictionaries) the credentials for the requested passwordID.

```
credentials = await CredentialsManager.get_credential_from_id(<passwordID>)
```

### update_credential

`async def update_credential(self, credentials_dict: dict) -> bool:`

Update credentials is used to update existing entries in Password State (the Vault), with whatever is passed to the function.

The return boolean is an indicator on successful update with the Vault.

```
existing_credentials = await CredentialsManager.get_credentials(<username>)

new_credentials = copy.deepcopy(existing_credentials)
new_credentials['Password'] = "Test-Example"

success_state = await CredentialsManager.update_credential(new_credentials)

if success_state == True:
    print("The password was successfully updated.")
else:
    print("The password update failed.")
```

### new_credentials

`async def new_credentials(self, credentials_dict: dict) -> bool:`

New credentials creates a new password entry within Password State (the Vault)

The credentials_dict [parameter](https://github.com/Whitecap-DNA/WCP-Library/wiki/Credentials-%E2%80%90-Expected-Dictionaries) is required.

It's essentially easier to get an existing credential using [get_credential()](https://github.com/Whitecap-DNA/WCP-Library/wiki/Credentials-%E2%80%90-Asynchronous#get_credentials) and modifying it to contain the new passwords information.

The return boolean is an indicator on successful entry with the Vault.

```
existing_credentials = await CredentialsManager.get_credentials(<username>)

new_credentials = copy.deepcopy(existing_credentials)
new_credentials['UserName'] = "Test-User-Example"
new_credentials['Password'] = "Test-Pass-Example"
new_credentials['Notes'] = "This is a test connection for the wiki"

success_state = await CredentialsManager.new_credential(new_credentials)

if success_state == True:
    print("The password was successfully saved in the Vault.")
else:
    print("The password entry failed.")
```